passages.text: Solid 1H25 with Better 2H Outlook and T Thesistntact; Reiterate Buy

SF Intra City reported solid 1H25 with total revenues \(+49\%\) yoy to Rmb10.2bn, \(5\%\) above ours, driven by \(4 / 11\%\) beat in to- B intra- city and last- mile revenues. Non- IFRS profit inline with ours at Rmb160mn or \(1.6\%\) NM (1.0% in 1H24). Into 2H25, management observed stronger 3Q vs. 2Q on intensifying food delivery competition in Jul/Aug and we expect decent momentum of to- B intra- city and last- mile order volume to extend into 4Q on ecommerce promotional season and ongoing adoption for on- demand retail. Riding on external positives such as ongoing platform decentralization, increasing brand concentration and more rider supply, we believe SF Intra City will remain best positioned as the leading 3P on- demand delivery provider with proven execution capabilities in offering full- chain merchant solutions, driving faster lower- tier city penetration and retaining quality riders. Post revision, we adjust TP to HK \(22 (from HK\) 21), based on 0.7x (unchanged) on FY26E revenue of Rmb25.9bn. Reiterate Buy.

Earnings revision - We raise FY25- 27E revenues by \(+4.5 / + 3.5 / + 4.2\%\) to Rmb21.9/25.9/30.4bn to reflect faster intra- city and last- mile order volume in 2H25 and sustainable growth in the medium term. We also fine- tuned our non- IFRS profit margin at 1.4/1.8/2.4% in FY25- 27E thanks to ongoing operating leverage.

Positive industry outlook - Management is positive on favorable industry tailwinds for on- demand delivery riding on structural behavioral changes for younger generation, platform decentralization and increasing brand concentration that boost positioning of third- party on- demand delivery players esp. SF Intra City.

Merchant and category performance - By end of 1H25, number of LTM active merchants reached 850K, growing strongly by \(55\%\) yoy. In terms of categories, revenue from tea beverage delivery increased by \(105\%\) yoy, while supermarket, convenient stores, pharmaceuticals and maternal products achieved high double- digit yoy growth.

Stable rider pool - No. of annual active riders further increased to 1.14mn with average daily order per active rider increasing by \(38\%\) yoy in Jun. Management fully ramped up rider subsidies after entry of JD food delivery in Apr but has scaled back in May to normalized level due to more new riders available in the market with more effective rider management in terms of welfare, upstream opportunities and corporate culture.

Faster market share gain in KA merchants and consumers. Improving operating efficiency to achieve LT target earlier.
Stable market share in KA merchants and consumers. Continued profitability driven by higher fulfillment efficiency.
Declining market share in KA merchants and consumers. Deteriorating unit economics due to competition.

Established in Jun 2016, SF Intra- City originated as a business unit of SF Holding Group that focuses on intra- city on- demand delivery services. From 2019, SF Intra- City began operating as an independent legal entity, with a mission to "bring enjoyable lifestyle to your fingertips". As a third- party on- demand delivery service platform, SF Intra- City fulfills orders acquired from non- related parties.

We rate SF Intra- City (SFIC) shares a Buy. Despite a fragmented market and keener competition, SFIC has the profile in our view to seize on- demand retail market opportunities. Drivers include its 1) 3P position (broader customer base), 2) multi- scenario model (high double- digit YoY % in non- food categories), 3) new services (delivery options, parcel collection), 4) synergies with SF Holding (40% revis mix), 5) early- mover edge in lower- tier cities. Scale and better fulfillment efficiency have enabled SFIC to turn around earlier than peers, to be on track to meet its long- term margin target of 3- 5%.

Our TP of HK\$22 is set at 0.7x 2026E PS, the average of 1) CN logistics peers with a similar margin profile; and 2) CN local services peers (internet players). We adopt a PS methodology to reflect the company's user base/order volume expansion and short history of profitability, and it is in line with the approach we use for close comps.

Key downside risks that could impede the SF Intra- City stock from reaching our TP include: 1) soft macro and local consumption; 2) intensified competition impacting service fees per order; 3) regulatory adjustments associated with flexible rider network; 4) and earnings fluctuations on a thin margin profile.

Investment Ratings: Citi Research investment ratings are Buy, Neutral and Sell. Our ratings are a function of analyst expectations of expected total return ("ETR") and risk. ETR is the sum of the forecast price appreciation (or depreciation) plus the dividend yield for a stock within the next 12 months. The target price is based on a 12 month time horizon. The Investment rating definitions are: Buy (1) ETR of \(15\%\) or more or \(25\%\) or more for High risk stocks; and Sell (3) for negative ETR. Any covered stock not assigned a Buy or a Sell is a Neutral (2).
